**Feature Details & Q&A**

**1. Password Storage & Autofill** ✅

Password Manager saves credentials when a user logs into any website and automatically fills them in on return visits.

**Q: Do passwords sync across all devices?**
A: Yes — sync is enabled. Any device where the user signs into Edge with their work account gets all saved passwords.

**Q: Can passwords be exported as a backup?**
A: Yes — passwords can be exported as a CSV file. Device authentication is required before export.

**Q: Can existing passwords be imported from other browsers?**
A: Yes — passwords from Chrome or any browser can be imported via CSV directly into Edge.

**Q: Can passwords be migrated from Chrome to Edge?**
A: Yes — export from Chrome, import into Edge. Once migrated, all passwords come under EPM control.

---

**2. Password Monitor** ✅

Password Monitor checks all saved passwords for security risks — leaked, reused and weak passwords.

**Q: What does Password Monitor check?**
A: Three things — leaked passwords found in known data breaches, reused passwords used across multiple sites, and weak passwords that are easy to guess.

**Q: Was this tested?**
A: Yes — scan detected 1 leaked password, 376 reused passwords and 18 weak passwords during evaluation.

**Q: Does it show which sites are affected?**
A: Yes — shows exactly which accounts have reused or compromised passwords.

**Q: Does it suggest fixing the issue?**
A: Yes — a direct "Change" button takes the user straight to that website's password change page.

**Q: Does it send email alerts when a breach is detected?**
A: No — checked email after breach was detected during testing. No email notification was received. Alert appears inside Edge settings only.

**Q: Can admin enforce this feature?**
A: Yes — confirmed via edge://policy. Once enabled by admin, users cannot turn it off.

---

**3. Azure AD Single Sign-On (SSO)** ✅

SSO allows users to sign in once with their work account and access all connected apps automatically without entering credentials again.

**Q: Which apps does SSO work on?**
A: Confirmed working on portal.office.com and non-Microsoft apps — JIRA, Confluence and Bitbucket.

**Q: Does the user need to do anything to enable it?**
A: No — works automatically when Edge is signed in with the work account on a company device.

**Q: Do users need to verify MFA for every app?**
A: No — MFA verified once for JIRA. Confluence and Bitbucket then signed in automatically in the same session.

**Q: Does SSO work on Chrome?**
A: Yes — Chrome signed in automatically via "Connected to Windows" on company-joined devices.

**Q: What security controls exist on SSO?**
A: 8 Conditional Access policies are active — portal.azure.com required additional authentication while everyday apps signed in automatically.

---

**4. Extension Monitoring** ✅

Extension Monitoring gives IT admins visibility into all browser extensions installed by employees across the organisation.

**Q: What does Extension Monitoring show?**
A: A list of all 30 extensions installed across company devices, with user count for each extension.

**Q: Why does this matter?**
A: Browser extensions can be a security risk. Monitoring helps IT see what is installed before it becomes a problem.

**Q: Can admin see which employee has which extension?**
A: No — only total user count is visible, not individual users.

**Q: Can admin block an extension from this screen?**
A: No — blocking requires a separate Configuration Policy. This screen is visibility only.

**Q: Does it show risk level of extensions?**
A: No — only extension ID and user count are shown.

